		h4#DATAProperties: strong Customization by using DATA Properties
		p This jSlider options are managed using "data-*" properties. You can add them to the wrapper as below:
		pre
			code.html
				| &lt;div id="slider1" class="jSlider" data-navigation="always" data-indicator="none"&gt;
		p Here is the document about "data-*" options:
		ul.data-properties
			li
				strong data-navigation: 
				| this manages the display of previous / next buttons.
				br
				| This can be set to "always", "none" or "hover". 
				br
				| "hover" is set by default which means the buttons will appear when users move their mouse hover the slider.
				br
				em On mobile, "hover" is equal to "none"
			li
				strong data-indicator: 
				| this manages the display of pagination buttons at the bottom of the slider.
				br
				| This can be set to "always", "none" or "hover".
				br
				| "always" is set by default.
				br
				em On mobile, "hover" is equal to "none"
			li
				strong data-speed: 
				| this manages transition speed of the slider in milliseconds.
				br
				| The default value is "500".
			li
				strong data-delay: 
				| this manages autoplay delay time between each transition of the slider in milliseconds.
				br
				| The default value is "5000". (5 seconds)
				br
				| If you do not want the autoplay, set it to "0" (zero)
			li
				strong data-transition: 
				| this manages transition type of the slider.
				br
				| This can be set to "slide" or "fade". 
				br
				| "slide" is set by default.
			li
				strong data-loop: 
				| this manages slide loop. If set to "true", when the slider reach to the end the next slide will be first slide. Vice versa.
				br
				| This can be set to "true" or "false". 
				br
				| "false" is set by default.
				br
				em "true" is best use for fade effect &amp; in background mode.
			li
				strong data-group: 
				| this manages slide group. You will define the group of elements in each slide. This is a specialize property for gallery mode. 
				| In "fade" transition, the value is always "1".
				br
				| The default value is "1".
		
		hr
		h3#cssFiles
			strong B) CSS Files and Structure 
			| - 
			a(href="#toc") top

		p Normally, the CSS of jSlider is just fine. You will not need to modify it except the slider dimension 
			| (width &amp; height), the display of the buttons (previous / next buttons &amp; pagination buttons.)

		p:strong You are recommended not to modify the "jSlider.css" file which is the main core CSS file of jSlider. 
			| It contains many important CSS rules.

		p To specify the slider dimension &amp; modify the previous / next buttons as well as the pagination buttons at the bottom of the slider, 
			| I suggest you to use another CSS file &amp; override the CSS rules.

		p: strong Slider dimension
			br
			| The slider width &amp; height are managed by using CSS rule. You can use reponsive rules to resize the slider 
			| width &amp; height for each screen size.
			br
			| Auto height: You can the slider height to AUTO. The slider height will automatically set to the height of 
			| the first image in the first slide.
		

		hr
		
		h3#javascript
			strong C) JavaScript 
			| - 
			a(href="#toc") top
		
		p Acctually, you don't need to do Javascript code except you have to generate the slider from Ajax content or 
			| you have to force the slider to move to the specific slide.
			br
			| Below is the list of API functions:

		p: strong Methods
		ul.data-properties
			li
				strong sliderInit: 
				| generate a new slider. Remember that, you should not have class "jSlider" in the wrapper. 
				| You can specify the slider options in the function *.
				pre $('#sliderId').sliderInit(<em>{settings}</em>);
			li
				strong sliderStop: 
				| cancel autoplay
				pre $('#sliderId').sliderStop();
			li
				strong sliderGo: 
				| go to next or previous slide.
				pre $('#sliderId').sliderStop(direction);
				| You must specify the 
				strong direction
				| value (1 or -1): go forward 1, go backward -1.
			li
				strong sliderUpdate: 
				| go to a specific slide
				pre $('#sliderId').sliderUpdate(index);
				| You must specify the slide 
				strong index. 
				| The first slide index is "0" (zero).
		
		p *About 
			em settings: 
			| {settings} is an object value which is the same as "data-*" properties mentioned earlier in the 
			a(href="#DATAProperties") DATA Properties. 
			| Below is the default settings.
		pre 
			code.js {
				|
				|     'navigation': 'hover',       /* hover | always | none */
				|     'indicator':  'always',      /* hover | always | none */
				|     'speed':      500,
				|     'delay':      5000,
				|     'transition': 'slide',       /* slide | fade */
				|     'loop':       false,         /* false | true */
				|     'group':      1
				| }
		
		p: strong Events:
		ul.data-properties
			li
				strong slideCreated: 
				| this event is fired when the slider is created.
				pre 
					code.js $('#sliderId').on('slideCreated', function(evt) {
						|
						|     /* do something */
						| });
			li
				strong slideStart: 
				| this event is fired when the slider begin a transition.
				pre 
					code.js $('#sliderId').on('slideStart', function(evt) {
						|
						|     /* do something */
						| });
			li
				strong slideComplete: 
				| this event is fired when the slider finish a transition. You can access the current slide index in event value.
				pre 
					code.js $('#sliderId').on('slideComplete', function(evt) {
						|
						|     alert(evt.current);    /* return the current slide index */
						| });
			li
				strong slideCancelAutoPlay: 
				| this event is fired when the autoplay is canceled.
				pre 
					code.js $('#sliderId').on('slideCancelAutoPlay', function(evt) {
						|
						|     /* do something */
						| });
		
